---
import Base from '../layouts/base.astro';
import CtaSection from '../components/blocks/CtaSection.astro';
---

<Base
  title="Security — Beebeeb"
  description="How Beebeeb encrypts your files: AES-256-GCM, HKDF, OPAQUE, X25519. Plus tamper-evident audit log, cryptographic share revocation, compromised-password rejection, step-up re-auth, and SAS-verified peer transfers. Zero-knowledge by architecture. EU-only infrastructure."
  path="/security"
>

  <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
       HERO
       ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <section class="px-8 pt-[72px] pb-16 text-center relative" style="background: linear-gradient(180deg, var(--color-amber-bg) 0%, var(--color-paper) 85%);">
    <div class="section-label bb-fade-up">Zero-knowledge architecture</div>
    <h1 class="text-[56px] leading-[1.05] font-bold tracking-[-0.03em] mt-3.5 max-w-[900px] mx-auto bb-fade-up bb-delay-1">
      What we can see: <span class="text-amber-deep">nothing.</span>
    </h1>
    <p class="text-base text-ink-2 mt-[22px] max-w-[640px] mx-auto leading-relaxed bb-fade-up bb-delay-2">
      Beebeeb is zero-knowledge by architecture, not by promise. Your files are encrypted on your device before they leave it. We never see your data, your filenames, or your keys. Even under a court order, we have nothing useful to hand over.
    </p>
    <div class="flex gap-3 justify-center mt-8 flex-wrap bb-fade-up bb-delay-3">
      <span class="inline-flex px-3 py-1.5 bg-paper border border-line rounded-md font-mono text-[11px] text-ink-3">AES-256-GCM</span>
      <span class="inline-flex px-3 py-1.5 bg-paper border border-line rounded-md font-mono text-[11px] text-ink-3">HKDF-SHA256</span>
      <span class="inline-flex px-3 py-1.5 bg-paper border border-line rounded-md font-mono text-[11px] text-ink-3">OPAQUE PAKE</span>
      <span class="inline-flex px-3 py-1.5 bg-paper border border-line rounded-md font-mono text-[11px] text-ink-3">X25519</span>
      <span class="inline-flex px-3 py-1.5 bg-paper border border-line rounded-md font-mono text-[11px] text-ink-3">Argon2id</span>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
       ENCRYPTION — How files are encrypted
       ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <section class="px-8 py-20 bg-paper border-t border-line">
    <div class="max-w-[1000px] mx-auto">
      <div class="section-label bb-fade-up">File encryption</div>
      <h2 class="text-[40px] font-bold tracking-[-0.025em] mb-4 leading-tight bb-fade-up bb-delay-1">
        Every file. Every chunk. Individually encrypted.
      </h2>
      <p class="text-base text-ink-2 max-w-[680px] mb-12 leading-relaxed bb-fade-up bb-delay-2">
        When you upload a file, it never leaves your device as plaintext. The encryption pipeline runs entirely in your browser (via WebAssembly) or natively on desktop and mobile.
      </p>

      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-4 mb-10" data-stagger>
        <div class="p-6 border border-line rounded-lg bg-paper bb-fade-up">
          <div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-[10px] bg-amber-bg text-amber-deep border border-[oklch(0.86_0.07_90)] flex items-center justify-center mb-4">
            <svg class="w-[18px] h-[18px]" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.6" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><rect x="3" y="11" width="18" height="11" rx="2" ry="2"/><path d="M7 11V7a5 5 0 0 1 10 0v4"/></svg>
          </div>
          <div class="font-mono text-[10px] text-ink-3 uppercase tracking-[0.06em] mb-1">Cipher</div>
          <div class="text-lg font-bold tracking-tight mb-2">AES-256-GCM</div>
          <p class="text-[13px] text-ink-2 leading-relaxed">
            Authenticated encryption with associated data. Each chunk gets a unique nonce. Tamper detection is built into the cipher -- if a single bit is modified, decryption fails.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="p-6 border border-line rounded-lg bg-paper bb-fade-up">
          <div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-[10px] bg-amber-bg text-amber-deep border border-[oklch(0.86_0.07_90)] flex items-center justify-center mb-4">
            <svg class="w-[18px] h-[18px]" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.6" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"/><path d="M12 6v6l4 2"/></svg>
          </div>
          <div class="font-mono text-[10px] text-ink-3 uppercase tracking-[0.06em] mb-1">Key derivation</div>
          <div class="text-lg font-bold tracking-tight mb-2">HKDF-SHA256</div>
          <p class="text-[13px] text-ink-2 leading-relaxed">
            Every file gets its own encryption key, derived from your master key using HKDF with a unique salt. Compromising one file key reveals nothing about your master key or other file keys.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="p-6 border border-line rounded-lg bg-paper bb-fade-up">
          <div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-[10px] bg-amber-bg text-amber-deep border border-[oklch(0.86_0.07_90)] flex items-center justify-center mb-4">
            <svg class="w-[18px] h-[18px]" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.6" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M14 2H6a2 2 0 0 0-2 2v16a2 2 0 0 0 2 2h12a2 2 0 0 0 2-2V8z"/><polyline points="14 2 14 8 20 8"/></svg>
          </div>
          <div class="font-mono text-[10px] text-ink-3 uppercase tracking-[0.06em] mb-1">Filename encryption</div>
          <div class="text-lg font-bold tracking-tight mb-2">AES-SIV</div>
          <p class="text-[13px] text-ink-2 leading-relaxed">
            Filenames and folder names are encrypted separately with AES-SIV. The server sees only opaque identifiers. Your directory structure is invisible to us.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Encryption flow -->
      <div class="border border-line rounded-xl bg-paper-2 p-8 bb-reveal-scale">
        <div class="font-mono text-[10px] text-ink-3 uppercase tracking-[0.06em] mb-5">Encryption pipeline</div>
        <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row items-center gap-4 md:gap-0">
          <div class="flex-1 text-center px-3">
            <div class="w-14 h-14 rounded-xl bg-paper border border-line mx-auto flex items-center justify-center shadow-1 mb-3">
              <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-ink-2" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M14 2H6a2 2 0 0 0-2 2v16a2 2 0 0 0 2 2h12a2 2 0 0 0 2-2V8z"/><polyline points="14 2 14 8 20 8"/></svg>
            </div>
            <div class="text-[13px] font-semibold mb-1">Your file</div>
            <div class="text-[11px] text-ink-3">Plaintext on device</div>
          </div>

          <svg class="w-8 h-5 text-ink-3 shrink-0 hidden md:block" viewBox="0 0 32 20"><path d="M0 10h28M24 5l4 5-4 5" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5"/></svg>
          <svg class="w-5 h-8 text-ink-3 shrink-0 md:hidden" viewBox="0 0 20 32"><path d="M10 0v28M5 24l5 4 5-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5"/></svg>

          <div class="flex-1 text-center px-3">
            <div class="w-14 h-14 rounded-xl bg-amber-bg border border-[oklch(0.86_0.07_90)] mx-auto flex items-center justify-center shadow-1 mb-3">
              <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-amber-deep" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><rect x="3" y="11" width="18" height="11" rx="2" ry="2"/><path d="M7 11V7a5 5 0 0 1 10 0v4"/></svg>
            </div>
            <div class="text-[13px] font-semibold mb-1">Encrypt + chunk</div>
            <div class="text-[11px] text-ink-3">AES-256-GCM per chunk</div>
          </div>

          <svg class="w-8 h-5 text-ink-3 shrink-0 hidden md:block" viewBox="0 0 32 20"><path d="M0 10h28M24 5l4 5-4 5" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5"/></svg>
          <svg class="w-5 h-8 text-ink-3 shrink-0 md:hidden" viewBox="0 0 20 32"><path d="M10 0v28M5 24l5 4 5-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5"/></svg>

          <div class="flex-1 text-center px-3">
            <div class="w-14 h-14 rounded-xl bg-paper border border-line mx-auto flex items-center justify-center shadow-1 mb-3">
              <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-ink-2" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M18 10h-1.26A8 8 0 1 0 9 20h9a5 5 0 0 0 0-10z"/></svg>
            </div>
            <div class="text-[13px] font-semibold mb-1">Upload ciphertext</div>
            <div class="text-[11px] text-ink-3">Only encrypted blobs</div>
          </div>

          <svg class="w-8 h-5 text-ink-3 shrink-0 hidden md:block" viewBox="0 0 32 20"><path d="M0 10h28M24 5l4 5-4 5" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5"/></svg>
          <svg class="w-5 h-8 text-ink-3 shrink-0 md:hidden" viewBox="0 0 20 32"><path d="M10 0v28M5 24l5 4 5-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5"/></svg>

          <div class="flex-1 text-center px-3">
            <div class="w-14 h-14 rounded-xl bg-paper border border-line mx-auto flex items-center justify-center shadow-1 mb-3">
              <div class="flex gap-1">
                {['FSN', 'AMS'].map(r => (
                  <span class="font-mono text-[8px] text-ink-3 font-semibold">{r}</span>
                ))}
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="text-[13px] font-semibold mb-1">Stored in EU</div>
            <div class="text-[11px] text-ink-3">Falkenstein + Amsterdam</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
       KEY HIERARCHY
       ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <section class="px-8 py-20 bg-paper-2 border-t border-line">
    <div class="max-w-[900px] mx-auto">
      <div class="section-label text-center bb-fade-up">Key hierarchy</div>
      <h2 class="text-[40px] font-bold tracking-[-0.025em] text-center mb-4 leading-tight bb-fade-up bb-delay-1">
        One password. Millions of keys.
      </h2>
      <p class="text-base text-ink-2 text-center max-w-[620px] mx-auto mb-14 bb-fade-up bb-delay-2">
        Your password is the root of everything. It never leaves your device. From it, we derive a hierarchy of keys -- each with a single purpose, each isolated from the others.
      </p>

      <!-- Key hierarchy diagram -->
      <div class="key-hierarchy bb-reveal-scale bb-delay-2">
        <!-- Level 0: Password -->
        <div class="flex justify-center mb-2">
          <div class="key-node key-node--root">
            <div class="key-node__icon">
              <svg class="w-5 h-5" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.6" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><rect x="3" y="11" width="18" height="11" rx="2" ry="2"/><path d="M7 11V7a5 5 0 0 1 10 0v4"/></svg>
            </div>
            <div>
              <div class="key-node__label">Your password</div>
              <div class="key-node__sub">Never sent to server. Not even as a hash.</div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Connector -->
        <div class="flex justify-center">
          <div class="key-connector">
            <div class="key-connector__line"></div>
            <div class="key-connector__badge">Argon2id</div>
            <div class="key-connector__line"></div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Level 1: Master key -->
        <div class="flex justify-center mb-2">
          <div class="key-node key-node--master">
            <div class="key-node__icon key-node__icon--amber">
              <svg class="w-5 h-5" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.6" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="m21 2-2 2m-7.61 7.61a5.5 5.5 0 1 1-7.778 7.778 5.5 5.5 0 0 1 7.777-7.777zm0 0L15.5 7.5m0 0 3 3L22 7l-3-3m-3.5 3.5L19 4"/></svg>
            </div>
            <div>
              <div class="key-node__label">Master key</div>
              <div class="key-node__sub">256-bit. Lives only in device memory. Zeroed after use.</div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Connector: fan-out -->
        <div class="flex justify-center">
          <div class="key-connector">
            <div class="key-connector__line"></div>
            <div class="key-connector__badge">HKDF-SHA256</div>
            <div class="key-connector__line"></div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Level 2: Derived keys -->
        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-3 gap-3">
          <div class="key-node key-node--leaf">
            <div class="key-node__icon key-node__icon--small">
              <svg class="w-4 h-4" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.6" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M14 2H6a2 2 0 0 0-2 2v16a2 2 0 0 0 2 2h12a2 2 0 0 0 2-2V8z"/><polyline points="14 2 14 8 20 8"/></svg>
            </div>
            <div>
              <div class="key-node__label text-[13px]">File keys</div>
              <div class="key-node__sub">Unique per file. Derived with file-specific salt.</div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="key-node key-node--leaf">
            <div class="key-node__icon key-node__icon--small">
              <svg class="w-4 h-4" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.6" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M22 19a2 2 0 0 1-2 2H4a2 2 0 0 1-2-2V5a2 2 0 0 1 2-2h5l2 3h9a2 2 0 0 1 2 2z"/></svg>
            </div>
            <div>
              <div class="key-node__label text-[13px]">Folder keys</div>
              <div class="key-node__sub">Wraps file keys within a folder. Shared via X25519.</div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="key-node key-node--leaf">
            <div class="key-node__icon key-node__icon--small">
              <svg class="w-4 h-4" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.6" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M20 21v-2a4 4 0 0 0-4-4H8a4 4 0 0 0-4 4v2"/><circle cx="12" cy="7" r="4"/></svg>
            </div>
            <div>
              <div class="key-node__label text-[13px]">Identity keys</div>
              <div class="key-node__sub">X25519 keypair for receiving shared folders.</div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Properties -->
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-3 mt-10">
        <div class="flex gap-3 p-4 border border-line rounded-lg bg-paper bb-fade-up">
          <div class="w-7 h-7 rounded-full bg-[oklch(0.94_0.06_155)] text-[oklch(0.35_0.12_155)] flex items-center justify-center shrink-0 mt-0.5">
            <svg class="w-3.5 h-3.5" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>
          </div>
          <div>
            <div class="text-[13px] font-semibold mb-0.5">Forward secrecy</div>
            <div class="text-[12px] text-ink-2 leading-relaxed">Compromising one file key does not reveal other file keys or the master key.</div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="flex gap-3 p-4 border border-line rounded-lg bg-paper bb-fade-up">
          <div class="w-7 h-7 rounded-full bg-[oklch(0.94_0.06_155)] text-[oklch(0.35_0.12_155)] flex items-center justify-center shrink-0 mt-0.5">
            <svg class="w-3.5 h-3.5" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>
          </div>
          <div>
            <div class="text-[13px] font-semibold mb-0.5">Zero key storage</div>
            <div class="text-[12px] text-ink-2 leading-relaxed">Your master key is never stored anywhere -- not on disk, not on server. It exists only in memory, and is zeroed after use.</div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="flex gap-3 p-4 border border-line rounded-lg bg-paper bb-fade-up">
          <div class="w-7 h-7 rounded-full bg-[oklch(0.94_0.06_155)] text-[oklch(0.35_0.12_155)] flex items-center justify-center shrink-0 mt-0.5">
            <svg class="w-3.5 h-3.5" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>
          </div>
          <div>
            <div class="text-[13px] font-semibold mb-0.5">Memory safety</div>
            <div class="text-[12px] text-ink-2 leading-relaxed">The crypto engine is written in Rust. Key material is zeroized from memory using the <code class="font-mono text-[11px]">zeroize</code> crate.</div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="flex gap-3 p-4 border border-line rounded-lg bg-paper bb-fade-up">
          <div class="w-7 h-7 rounded-full bg-[oklch(0.94_0.06_155)] text-[oklch(0.35_0.12_155)] flex items-center justify-center shrink-0 mt-0.5">
            <svg class="w-3.5 h-3.5" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>
          </div>
          <div>
            <div class="text-[13px] font-semibold mb-0.5">No password transmission</div>
            <div class="text-[12px] text-ink-2 leading-relaxed">OPAQUE ensures your password is never sent to the server in any form -- not plaintext, not hashed, not derived.</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
       AUTHENTICATION — OPAQUE
       ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <section class="px-8 py-20 bg-paper border-t border-line">
    <div class="max-w-[1000px] mx-auto">
      <div class="section-label bb-fade-up">Authentication</div>
      <h2 class="text-[40px] font-bold tracking-[-0.025em] mb-4 leading-tight bb-fade-up bb-delay-1">
        Your password never leaves your device.
      </h2>
      <p class="text-base text-ink-2 max-w-[680px] mb-12 leading-relaxed bb-fade-up bb-delay-2">
        Most services hash your password and send the hash to a server. If that server is breached, the hash can be cracked. We use OPAQUE -- a Password-Authenticated Key Exchange protocol that proves you know the password without ever transmitting it.
      </p>

      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
        <div class="border border-line rounded-xl bg-paper-2 p-6 bb-fade-up">
          <div class="font-mono text-[10px] text-ink-3 uppercase tracking-[0.06em] mb-4">Traditional login</div>
          <div class="space-y-3">
            <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
              <div class="w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-paper-3 text-ink-3 flex items-center justify-center shrink-0">
                <svg class="w-3.5 h-3.5" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><line x1="18" y1="6" x2="6" y2="18"/><line x1="6" y1="6" x2="18" y2="18"/></svg>
              </div>
              <span class="text-[13px] text-ink-2">Password hashed client-side</span>
            </div>
            <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
              <div class="w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-paper-3 text-ink-3 flex items-center justify-center shrink-0">
                <svg class="w-3.5 h-3.5" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><line x1="18" y1="6" x2="6" y2="18"/><line x1="6" y1="6" x2="18" y2="18"/></svg>
              </div>
              <span class="text-[13px] text-ink-2">Hash sent to server for verification</span>
            </div>
            <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
              <div class="w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-paper-3 text-ink-3 flex items-center justify-center shrink-0">
                <svg class="w-3.5 h-3.5" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><line x1="18" y1="6" x2="6" y2="18"/><line x1="6" y1="6" x2="18" y2="18"/></svg>
              </div>
              <span class="text-[13px] text-ink-2">Server stores hash -- crackable if breached</span>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="border border-[oklch(0.86_0.07_90)] rounded-xl bg-amber-bg p-6 bb-fade-up">
          <div class="font-mono text-[10px] text-amber-deep uppercase tracking-[0.06em] mb-4">Beebeeb with OPAQUE</div>
          <div class="space-y-3">
            <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
              <div class="w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-[oklch(0.94_0.06_155)] text-[oklch(0.35_0.12_155)] flex items-center justify-center shrink-0">
                <svg class="w-3.5 h-3.5" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>
              </div>
              <span class="text-[13px] text-ink">Password stays on device entirely</span>
            </div>
            <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
              <div class="w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-[oklch(0.94_0.06_155)] text-[oklch(0.35_0.12_155)] flex items-center justify-center shrink-0">
                <svg class="w-3.5 h-3.5" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>
              </div>
              <span class="text-[13px] text-ink">Zero-knowledge proof of knowledge</span>
            </div>
            <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
              <div class="w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-[oklch(0.94_0.06_155)] text-[oklch(0.35_0.12_155)] flex items-center justify-center shrink-0">
                <svg class="w-3.5 h-3.5" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>
              </div>
              <span class="text-[13px] text-ink">Server breach reveals nothing usable</span>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
       SHARING — X25519 key exchange
       ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <section class="px-8 py-20 bg-paper-2 border-t border-line">
    <div class="max-w-[1000px] mx-auto">
      <div class="section-label bb-fade-up">Encrypted sharing</div>
      <h2 class="text-[40px] font-bold tracking-[-0.025em] mb-4 leading-tight bb-fade-up bb-delay-1">
        Share without exposing keys to the server.
      </h2>
      <p class="text-base text-ink-2 max-w-[680px] mb-12 leading-relaxed bb-fade-up bb-delay-2">
        When you share a folder with another user, the encryption key is wrapped specifically for their public key using X25519 Diffie-Hellman key exchange. The server transports the wrapped key but cannot unwrap it.
      </p>

      <!-- Sharing flow -->
      <div class="border border-line rounded-xl bg-paper p-8 bb-reveal-scale">
        <div class="font-mono text-[10px] text-ink-3 uppercase tracking-[0.06em] mb-6">Key exchange flow</div>
        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-5 gap-4 items-center">
          <!-- Alice -->
          <div class="text-center">
            <div class="w-12 h-12 rounded-full bg-amber-bg border border-[oklch(0.86_0.07_90)] mx-auto flex items-center justify-center mb-2">
              <span class="font-mono text-[11px] font-bold text-amber-deep">You</span>
            </div>
            <div class="text-[12px] font-semibold">Sender</div>
            <div class="text-[10px] text-ink-3">Has folder key</div>
          </div>

          <!-- Step 1 -->
          <div class="text-center">
            <div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-lg bg-paper-2 border border-line mx-auto flex items-center justify-center mb-2">
              <span class="font-mono text-[10px] font-bold text-ink-3">01</span>
            </div>
            <div class="text-[11px] text-ink-2 leading-tight">Fetch recipient's<br/>X25519 public key</div>
          </div>

          <!-- Step 2 -->
          <div class="text-center">
            <div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-lg bg-amber-bg border border-[oklch(0.86_0.07_90)] mx-auto flex items-center justify-center mb-2">
              <span class="font-mono text-[10px] font-bold text-amber-deep">02</span>
            </div>
            <div class="text-[11px] text-ink-2 leading-tight">Wrap folder key<br/>for recipient</div>
          </div>

          <!-- Step 3 -->
          <div class="text-center">
            <div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-lg bg-paper-2 border border-line mx-auto flex items-center justify-center mb-2">
              <span class="font-mono text-[10px] font-bold text-ink-3">03</span>
            </div>
            <div class="text-[11px] text-ink-2 leading-tight">Server stores<br/>wrapped key blob</div>
          </div>

          <!-- Bob -->
          <div class="text-center">
            <div class="w-12 h-12 rounded-full bg-paper-2 border border-line mx-auto flex items-center justify-center mb-2">
              <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-ink-3" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.6" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M20 21v-2a4 4 0 0 0-4-4H8a4 4 0 0 0-4 4v2"/><circle cx="12" cy="7" r="4"/></svg>
            </div>
            <div class="text-[12px] font-semibold">Recipient</div>
            <div class="text-[10px] text-ink-3">Unwraps with secret key</div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="mt-6 p-3 bg-paper-2 border border-line rounded-md">
          <div class="text-[12px] text-ink-2 leading-relaxed">
            The server never sees the folder key in plaintext. It stores a ciphertext blob that only the recipient's X25519 secret key can unwrap. If the server is compromised, the attacker gets encrypted blobs they cannot decrypt.
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
       DEFENSE IN DEPTH — Operational security
       ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <section class="px-8 py-20 bg-paper border-t border-line">
    <div class="max-w-[1000px] mx-auto">
      <div class="section-label bb-fade-up">Defense in depth</div>
      <h2 class="text-[40px] font-bold tracking-[-0.025em] mb-4 leading-tight bb-fade-up bb-delay-1">
        Encryption is the floor, not the ceiling.
      </h2>
      <p class="text-base text-ink-2 max-w-[680px] mb-12 leading-relaxed bb-fade-up bb-delay-2">
        Strong cryptography stops a server breach from leaking your files. It does not, on its own, stop a stolen credential, an unrevoked share, or a tampered server log. Here is what we do about each of those.
      </p>

      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4" data-stagger>

        <!-- Hash-chained audit log -->
        <div class="p-6 border border-line rounded-lg bg-paper bb-fade-up">
          <div class="flex items-start gap-4 mb-3">
            <div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-[10px] bg-amber-bg text-amber-deep border border-[oklch(0.86_0.07_90)] flex items-center justify-center shrink-0">
              <svg class="w-[18px] h-[18px]" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.6" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M10 13a5 5 0 0 0 7.54.54l3-3a5 5 0 0 0-7.07-7.07l-1.72 1.71"/><path d="M14 11a5 5 0 0 0-7.54-.54l-3 3a5 5 0 0 0 7.07 7.07l1.71-1.71"/></svg>
            </div>
            <div>
              <div class="font-mono text-[10px] text-ink-3 uppercase tracking-[0.06em] mb-1">Tamper-evident audit log</div>
              <div class="text-lg font-bold tracking-tight">Hash-chained, verifiable</div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <p class="text-[13px] text-ink-2 leading-relaxed mb-3">
            Every account event -- login, share, revocation, deletion -- is appended to a hash-chained log. Each entry includes the SHA-256 of the previous one, so removing or rewriting an event breaks the chain.
          </p>
          <p class="text-[13px] text-ink-2 leading-relaxed">
            You can verify the chain yourself at <code class="font-mono text-[11px] text-amber-deep">/audit/verify</code>. If we silently dropped an event, the endpoint would tell you.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Per-share revocation -->
        <div class="p-6 border border-line rounded-lg bg-paper bb-fade-up">
          <div class="flex items-start gap-4 mb-3">
            <div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-[10px] bg-amber-bg text-amber-deep border border-[oklch(0.86_0.07_90)] flex items-center justify-center shrink-0">
              <svg class="w-[18px] h-[18px]" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.6" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M3 6h18"/><path d="M19 6v14a2 2 0 0 1-2 2H7a2 2 0 0 1-2-2V6"/><path d="M8 6V4a2 2 0 0 1 2-2h4a2 2 0 0 1 2 2v2"/></svg>
            </div>
            <div>
              <div class="font-mono text-[10px] text-ink-3 uppercase tracking-[0.06em] mb-1">Per-share revocation</div>
              <div class="text-lg font-bold tracking-tight">Revoke = destroy the key</div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <p class="text-[13px] text-ink-2 leading-relaxed mb-3">
            Most "revoke share" buttons just flip a database flag. Ours destroys the wrapped key on the server. Without that wrapping, the recipient's device cannot derive the file key for any chunk it had not already downloaded.
          </p>
          <p class="text-[13px] text-ink-2 leading-relaxed">
            Each share gets its own key. Revoking one share never affects the others.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Compromised password rejection -->
        <div class="p-6 border border-line rounded-lg bg-paper bb-fade-up">
          <div class="flex items-start gap-4 mb-3">
            <div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-[10px] bg-amber-bg text-amber-deep border border-[oklch(0.86_0.07_90)] flex items-center justify-center shrink-0">
              <svg class="w-[18px] h-[18px]" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.6" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M10.29 3.86 1.82 18a2 2 0 0 0 1.71 3h16.94a2 2 0 0 0 1.71-3L13.71 3.86a2 2 0 0 0-3.42 0z"/><line x1="12" y1="9" x2="12" y2="13"/><line x1="12" y1="17" x2="12.01" y2="17"/></svg>
            </div>
            <div>
              <div class="font-mono text-[10px] text-ink-3 uppercase tracking-[0.06em] mb-1">Compromised password check</div>
              <div class="text-lg font-bold tracking-tight">HIBP at signup</div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <p class="text-[13px] text-ink-2 leading-relaxed mb-3">
            We can't recover this password, so you cannot use one that's already been leaked. At signup we check the first five characters of your password's SHA-1 against Have I Been Pwned's k-anonymity range API.
          </p>
          <p class="text-[13px] text-ink-2 leading-relaxed">
            Your full password never leaves your device. If a hash matches a known breach, signup is blocked until you choose another.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Step-up re-auth -->
        <div class="p-6 border border-line rounded-lg bg-paper bb-fade-up">
          <div class="flex items-start gap-4 mb-3">
            <div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-[10px] bg-amber-bg text-amber-deep border border-[oklch(0.86_0.07_90)] flex items-center justify-center shrink-0">
              <svg class="w-[18px] h-[18px]" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.6" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"/><polyline points="12 6 12 12 16 14"/></svg>
            </div>
            <div>
              <div class="font-mono text-[10px] text-ink-3 uppercase tracking-[0.06em] mb-1">Step-up re-auth</div>
              <div class="text-lg font-bold tracking-tight">Password again before destruction</div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <p class="text-[13px] text-ink-2 leading-relaxed mb-3">
            A grabbed session cookie shouldn't be enough to delete an account or wipe a folder. Destructive operations -- account deletion, bulk delete, share revocation, recovery-key rotation -- require a fresh OPAQUE re-authentication.
          </p>
          <p class="text-[13px] text-ink-2 leading-relaxed">
            The step-up is bound to the operation, time-limited, and logged in the audit chain.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- SAS-authenticated transfers -->
        <div class="p-6 border border-line rounded-lg bg-paper bb-fade-up md:col-span-2">
          <div class="flex items-start gap-4 mb-3">
            <div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-[10px] bg-amber-bg text-amber-deep border border-[oklch(0.86_0.07_90)] flex items-center justify-center shrink-0">
              <svg class="w-[18px] h-[18px]" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.6" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M11 5 6 9H2v6h4l5 4V5z"/><path d="M19.07 4.93a10 10 0 0 1 0 14.14M15.54 8.46a5 5 0 0 1 0 7.07"/></svg>
            </div>
            <div>
              <div class="font-mono text-[10px] text-ink-3 uppercase tracking-[0.06em] mb-1">Constellation peer transfers</div>
              <div class="text-lg font-bold tracking-tight">SAS-authenticated, end-to-end</div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <p class="text-[13px] text-ink-2 leading-relaxed mb-3">
            Constellation is our cross-platform peer transfer -- send from a phone to a stranger's laptop, no account needed on the receiving end. The two devices perform an X25519 key exchange and display a Short Authenticated String: a four-word code that both sides read aloud or compare on screen.
          </p>
          <p class="text-[13px] text-ink-2 leading-relaxed">
            If a man-in-the-middle has intercepted the exchange, the codes won't match. The file itself is encrypted end-to-end with the negotiated key; our relay sees only ciphertext and never holds the file at rest.
          </p>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

